           "rendered": "\n<h2 style=\"text-align: right;\">(&#1575;&#1604;&#1602;&#1585;&#1570;&#1606; (&#1776;&#1781;:&#1776;&#1778;</h2>\n<p><div class=\"wwm_socialshare_imagewrapper\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-4843\" src=\"https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02.png\" alt=\"Quranic Quotes Urdu #249\" width=\"2000\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02.png 2000w, https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02-744x744.png 744w, https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02-1200x1200.png 1200w, https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02-420x420.png 420w, https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02-768x768.png 768w, https://quranicquotes.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/quran_urdu_maida_02-1536x1536.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></div></p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: right;\">&#1575;&#1585;&#1583;&#1608;</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">&#1606;&#1740;&#1705;&#1740; &#1575;&#1608;&#1585; &#1662;&#1585;&#1729;&#1740;&#1586;&#1711;&#1575;&#1585;&#1740; &#1605;&#1740;&#1722; &#1575;&#1740;&#1705; &#1583;&#1608;&#1587;&#1585;&#1746; &#1705;&#1740; &#1575;&#1605;&#1583;&#1575;&#1583; &#1705;&#1585;&#1578;&#1746; &#1585;&#1729;&#1608; &#1575;&#1608;&#1585; &#1711;&#1606;&#1575;&#1729; &#1575;&#1608;&#1585;&#1592;&#1604;&#1605; &#1586;&#1740;&#1575;&#1583;&#1578;&#1740; &#1605;&#1740;&#1722; &#1605;&#1583;&#1583; &#1606;&#1729; &#1705;&#1585;&#1608; &#1575;&#1608;&#1585; &#1575;&#1604;&#1604;&#1729; &#1578;&#1593;&#1575;&#1604;&#1648;&#1740; &#1587;&#1746; &#1672;&#1585;&#1578;&#1746; &#1585;&#1729;&#1608;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>English</h3>\n<blockquote><p>O believers! Do not violate Allah&rsquo;s rituals &#761;of pilgrimage&#762;, the sacred months, the sacrificial animals, the &#761;offerings decorated with&#762; garlands, nor those &#761;pilgrims&#762; on their way to the Sacred House seeking their Lord&rsquo;s bounty and pleasure. When pilgrimage has ended, you are allowed to hunt. Do not let the hatred of a people who once barred you from the Sacred Mosque provoke you to transgress. Cooperate with one another in goodness and righteousness, and do not cooperate in sin and transgression. And be mindful of Allah. Surely Allah is severe in punishment.</p></blockquote>\n<ul class=\"wwm_social_share wwm_top_right\"><li class=\"wwm_facebook\"></li><li class=\"wwm_twitter\"></li><li class=\"wwm_pinit\"></li><li class=\"wwm_tumblr\"></li></ul><input type=\"hidden\" id=\"wwm_mode\" value=\"1\"/>",
